    <h1 id="transactions">Transactions</h1>
    <h2 id="assigning-transactions">Assigning to Envelope</h2>
    Assigning transactions to envelopes can be done two different ways:
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Edit Transaction</strong> - Double click or highlight and click "Edit" and then select the Envelope before saving.<br/>
       <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/assign-transaction.png"/></li>
       <li><strong>Drag and Drop</strong> - Simpy click and hold the mouse button down while you drag the transaction over an envelope.<br/>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/assign-drag-drop-transaction.png"/></li>
      </ol>
      <h2 id="splitting-transactions">Splitting</h2>
      <p>Let's say you go to Target and spend $75.00.  $25.00 of this was for groceries and the rest was for clothing.  The transaction that shows up in your account is $75.00 but needs to be "split" across multiple envelopes.  Splitting a transaction is easy.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the transaction for editing by double clicking it or highlighting and clicking "Edit" button.</li>
        <li>Click the "Split" button.  You will see an envelope line item added to the transation and "Amount" column appear.</li>
        <li>Specify the envelope and amount for each "split".  The total of the split amounts should add up to the transaction amount.</li>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/split-transaction.png"/>
        <h2 id="allocating-income">Allocating Income</h2>
        <p>Income transactions (i.e. your paycheck) should be placed in the "Unallocated Income" envelope first.  It is recommended to setup a <a href="#filters">Filter</a> to allow income transactions to be assigned automatically.  When you are ready to allocate your income, simply click the Unallocated Income envelope and then click the "Allocate Income Now" button at the top.</p>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/allocate-income.png"/>
        <p>An "Allocate Income" window will open prompting you to specify how to allocate the income.  The envelope amounts should add up to the total allocation amount.  If you have added Incomes, you should have "Allocation Plans" available on the top.  You can select the appropriate allocation plan and then click "Apply" to prepopulate the envelope amounts.</p>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/allocate-income-form.png"/>
        <h2 id="filters"> Filters</h2>
        <p>Transaction filters allow for automatic assignment of new transactions to predefined envelopes.  This saves you time so you don't have to assign recurring transactions that you already know about.  For instance, you can setup filters for your monthly bills (mortgage, cell phone, etc.) so that those transactions will automatically be assigned to the correct envelope.</p>
        <p>To add or edit filters, click the "Filters" button from the Transactions screen (top right).</p>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/filters.png"/>
        <p>You can then add, edit and/or remove filters and then click "Save".  The transaction name you enter does not have to match new transactions exactly but it should at least be close.  For instance, "SHELL" would match a new incoming transaction of "SHELL OIL STORE #5929.  Also, enter the amount of the transaction is optional.  If an amount is specified, only new transactions of that exact amount will be filtered.  If no amount is specified, only the transaction name will be used for matching.</p>
        <img class="img-thumbnail" src="{{assets}}/images/filters-edit.png"/>
      </div>
